VALUES

('dovetail',
 'Dovetail',
 'AI-powered research repository that synthesises customer insights from interviews, surveys, and support data',
 'Dovetail is a user research repository and analysis platform that helps product and design teams make sense of qualitative data at scale. Teams upload interview recordings, survey responses, support tickets, NPS comments, and sales call transcripts, and Dovetail AI automatically tags themes, groups insights by pattern, and surfaces the most frequently mentioned issues across all data sources. The core problem Dovetail solves is research fragmentation: insights from a usability study done in January exist in one researcher''s notes, customer feedback from March is in a spreadsheet, and support trends are in a separate tool - none of it connected. Dovetail creates a searchable repository where all customer intelligence is centralised, tagged, and queryable by any team member. Highlights from interviews can be clipped into short video or audio segments and shared directly in Slack or Notion, making it easy to communicate customer pain points to engineering or executive teams with raw evidence rather than a slide deck summary. The AI sentiment analysis identifies patterns across hundreds of feedback entries that would take a researcher days to process manually. Dovetail integrates with Zoom, Loom, Google Meet, Intercom, Zendesk, and Productboard. It is used by research teams at Spotify, Amplitude, and Atlassian to centralise customer intelligence and make it accessible to the whole product organisation.',
 NULL,
 'https://dovetail.com',
 'https://dovetail.com',
 ARRAY['ux-research', 'user-research', 'product', 'qualitative-research', 'insights'],
 'freemium',
 true,
 0.00,
 4.6, 1840,
 false, false, false,
 ARRAY['AI automatically tags themes across interview transcripts and survey data', 'Centralises all customer intelligence into one searchable repository', 'Video and audio highlight clipping makes insights shareable across the org', 'Integrates with Zoom, Intercom, Zendesk, and Productboard'],
 ARRAY['Most powerful for teams with dedicated researchers generating significant qualitative data', 'Free plan limits project and storage capacity meaningfully', 'Analysis quality depends on tagging consistency across the team'],
 ARRAY['Centralising user interview insights for a product team across multiple studies', 'Building a searchable customer evidence library from support and NPS data', 'Sharing video highlights from customer calls with engineering and leadership teams']),

('maze',
 'Maze',
 'Rapid user testing platform for prototype testing, surveys, and card sorting without a researcher',
 'Maze is a rapid user testing platform that lets product and design teams run unmoderated usability tests, prototype tests, and surveys without scheduling research sessions. Connect a Figma, InVision, or Marvel prototype and Maze distributes it to participants from its built-in panel of over 100,000 testers, or to your own recruited participants via a sharable link. Participants complete tasks on the prototype in their own time, and Maze records where they click, where they get stuck, and how long each task takes. The quantitative output - task success rates, time-on-task, misclick rates, and heatmaps - is available in a results dashboard within hours rather than the days or weeks of scheduling and conducting moderated sessions. Maze also includes tree testing for information architecture validation and card sorting for navigation structure decisions, plus a survey builder for collecting preference data. The AI analysis layer identifies the highest-impact usability issues from task completion patterns and open-text responses, surfacing a prioritised list of problems without requiring the researcher to manually review every session recording. Maze integrates with Figma, Notion, Jira, and Slack for distributing results. It is used by design and product teams at Uber, Brex, and Strava for continuous, lightweight usability validation alongside regular design iteration.',
 NULL,
 'https://maze.co',
 'https://maze.co',
 ARRAY['ux-research', 'usability-testing', 'prototype-testing', 'user-testing', 'product'],
 'freemium',
 true,
 0.00,
 4.5, 2310,
 false, false, false,
 ARRAY['Unmoderated prototype testing delivers results in hours, not weeks', 'Built-in panel of 100,000+ testers removes participant recruitment friction', 'Quantitative task data - success rates, heatmaps, misclick rates - is actionable immediately', 'Integrates directly with Figma for prototype connection without export'],
 ARRAY['Unmoderated format misses the "why" behind user behaviour visible in moderated sessions', 'Panel quality varies by niche demographic and professional segments', 'Tree testing and card sorting features are less advanced than dedicated tools'],
