('sprig',
 'Sprig',
 'In-product research platform for capturing user feedback and behaviour in real time during the actual experience',
 'Sprig is an in-product user research platform that captures feedback and behavioural signals from users while they are actively using the product - not after the session in a separate survey. The platform embeds lightweight micro-surveys that appear contextually during the product experience - a five-second satisfaction question after completing a task, a feature request prompt after a new feature is used, or a churn exit survey triggered when a user cancels. Because the prompt appears in context, response rates are significantly higher than email surveys and the feedback is more specific and actionable. Sprig also includes session recordings and heatmaps to capture behavioural data alongside attitudinal survey data, allowing teams to see not just what users say but what they actually do. The AI analysis layer processes open-text responses at scale - identifying sentiment trends, clustering feedback themes, and surfacing the top issues mentioned across thousands of responses without manual coding. Sprig integrates with Segment, Amplitude, Mixpanel, Figma, and Slack. Product teams use it for ongoing continuous discovery - running permanent in-product surveys that generate a constant stream of user intelligence rather than one-off research projects. Used by Notion, Loom, Dropbox, and PayPal for always-on user feedback collection integrated directly into the product experience.',
 NULL,
 'https://sprig.com',
 'https://sprig.com',
 ARRAY['ux-research', 'user-feedback', 'product', 'microsurveys', 'session-recording'],
 'freemium',
 true,
 0.00,
