('lyssna',
 'Lyssna',
 'Remote user research platform for preference testing, prototype testing, and interview recruitment',
 'Lyssna is a remote user research platform - formerly known as UsabilityHub - that covers the most common types of rapid, unmoderated research: first-click tests, preference tests, five-second tests, prototype tests, and surveys. First-click tests show a design and record where participants click first, validating whether the primary call to action or navigation is intuitive. Five-second tests expose a design for five seconds and ask what participants remembered, measuring immediate comprehension of a value proposition or page layout. Preference tests show two or three design options and ask which one participants prefer, with the option to collect reasoning. These quick-turn tests are designed to replace opinion-based design debates with evidence in hours rather than days. Lyssna''s participant panel covers over 690,000 people with demographic filtering by age, country, job role, and device type. The platform also includes a live interview module with integrated scheduling, consent management, and session recording, making it possible to run both quick unmoderated tests and deeper moderated interviews from a single tool. AI generates written summaries of test results and highlights the key findings without requiring manual analysis of every response. Lyssna is used by design teams at Canva, Shopify, and Square for rapid preference validation and concept testing early in the design process.',
 NULL,
 'https://lyssna.com',
 'https://lyssna.com',
 ARRAY['ux-research', 'usability-testing', 'preference-testing', 'user-testing', 'prototype-testing'],
 'freemium',
 true,
 0.00,
 4.4, 1120,
 false, false, false,
 ARRAY['First-click, five-second, and preference tests deliver results in hours', 'Panel of 690,000+ participants with demographic targeting', 'Covers both unmoderated tests and moderated live interviews in one platform', 'AI result summaries reduce manual analysis time significantly'],
 ARRAY['Five-second and preference tests provide directional data rather than deep insight', 'Live interview module is less mature than dedicated interview tools like Lookback', 'Free plan limits monthly test responses and panel access'],
