('optimal-workshop',
 'Optimal Workshop',
 'Information architecture research tools for card sorting, tree testing, and first-click testing',
 'Optimal Workshop is a suite of information architecture and navigation research tools used by UX researchers and designers to validate how users understand and navigate information structures. The three core tools cover the most important IA research methods. Treejack tests whether users can find information within a proposed navigation structure by presenting the tree as text without any visual design, isolating the structural logic from design influence. Optimal Sort runs card sorting studies where participants group content items into categories and name those categories, revealing the mental models users bring to a product''s content. Chalkmark runs first-click tests showing a design and asking participants to click where they would go first to complete a task, validating whether the most important actions are findable. A fourth tool, Questions, handles survey research for any research question that does not require behavioural observation. Optimal Workshop has a built-in participant panel for recruiting testers without sourcing participants independently. The analysis tools calculate agreement scores, dendrograms for card sort groupings, and success rates for treejack tasks, providing the statistical output that IA research decisions need to be defensible. Used by research teams at large organisations to validate information architecture before investing in development, and by consultants running IA audits for clients with complex navigation structures.',
 NULL,
 'https://optimalworkshop.com',
 'https://optimalworkshop.com',
 ARRAY['ux-research', 'information-architecture', 'card-sorting', 'tree-testing', 'user-testing'],
 'freemium',
 true,
 0.00,
 4.2, 780,
