('userlytics',
 'Userlytics',
 'Enterprise remote user testing platform with global panel access and AI video analysis',
 'Userlytics is a remote unmoderated and moderated user research platform used by enterprise product and UX teams for large-scale, high-quality usability testing. The platform provides access to a global panel of over 2 million participants with detailed demographic and professional filtering - age, country, device type, industry, job title, and screener questions that ensure only qualified participants complete the study. Studies can test websites, mobile apps, prototype designs, competitor products, or specific interface flows, with participants completing tasks while their screen, voice, and camera are recorded. Userlytics AI analyses video recordings to detect sentiment, flag moments of confusion or frustration, and generate written summaries of key findings across a participant set without requiring a researcher to watch every video in full. The platform supports both unmoderated studies where participants complete tasks independently and moderated live sessions where a researcher guides the participant in real time. The enterprise plan includes a dedicated customer success manager, custom SLA agreements, and integration with data warehouses and enterprise research stacks. Userlytics is used by enterprise research teams at Adobe, HP, and Visa who need to run large-scale international studies across multiple languages and device types with consistent quality.',
 NULL,
