('dscout',
 'Dscout',
 'Mobile diary study and remote research platform for capturing experiences in the real world',
 'Dscout is a remote research platform specialised in diary studies and in-context research - capturing user experiences as they happen in daily life rather than in a controlled lab or research session. Participants use the Dscout mobile app to complete research missions: recording short videos of their experience using a product, taking photos of how they perform a task, or answering questions triggered at specific moments throughout their day. This longitudinal approach captures the genuine, in-context experience that laboratory or session-based research misses - how a product fits into a user''s actual routine, the moments of frustration that occur over days of use rather than a single test session, and the environmental context that shapes how the product is used. Dscout Live is a moderated interview module that enables remote video interviews with participants, complementing diary study data with deeper qualitative probing. The platform includes participant recruitment from its own panel or management of externally recruited participants. Dscout AI analyses video diary entries and open-text responses to identify recurring themes and emotional signals across a participant set. Used by research teams at Google, Airbnb, and Johnson and Johnson for in-context research where the lived experience matters - product design for real-world conditions, service design, and innovation research where usage context is the primary research question.',
 NULL,
 'https://dscout.com',
