('respondent',
 'Respondent',
 'Professional participant recruitment platform for finding qualified B2B and specialist research participants',
 'Respondent is a participant recruitment marketplace that connects UX researchers and product teams with qualified research participants, particularly for hard-to-reach professional and specialist audiences. Most user research participant panels are consumer-focused, making it difficult to recruit software engineers, CFOs, healthcare workers, HR directors, or other professional personas who match a specific buyer profile. Respondent addresses this by maintaining a database of verified professionals who have provided their employment, role, and industry information and who participate in paid research sessions. Researchers post study requirements - target role, industry, company size, seniority, and screening questions - and Respondent matches and schedules participants who meet the criteria. Participants are compensated for their time at rates reflecting their professional value, which attracts higher-quality respondents than low-incentive panels. Studies can be conducted through the researcher''s preferred platform including Zoom, Lookback, or UserZoom, with Respondent handling recruitment, scheduling, incentive payments, and no-show protection. Respondent is used by B2B product teams, enterprise UX researchers, and market research firms that need specific professional profiles for interviews, usability tests, focus groups, and diary studies. The platform also handles participant verification and fraud prevention, which is a persistent challenge for self-serve recruitment at scale.',
 NULL,
 'https://respondent.io',
