('playbook-ux',
 'PlaybookUX',
 'Affordable unmoderated and moderated user testing with built-in participant panel and analysis tools',
 'PlaybookUX is a user testing platform that covers both unmoderated prototype and website tests and moderated live interview sessions at a price point accessible to smaller product and design teams. For unmoderated studies, researchers upload a prototype or URL, define tasks, and participants from the built-in panel complete sessions with screen, voice, and camera recording. For moderated research, PlaybookUX provides a video interview environment with session recording and a live note-taking panel. The built-in participant panel covers a range of demographic and professional profiles with screener questions to filter for specific personas. AI analysis transcribes all session recordings automatically, identifies key moments flagged by participant behaviour, and generates a summary of the most common themes across a set of sessions - reducing the manual analysis work required after data collection. PlaybookUX pricing is designed to be more affordable than enterprise alternatives like UserZoom or Userlytics, with per-session pricing that works for teams running occasional studies rather than continuous research programmes. The platform integrates with Figma for prototype testing and with Slack for sharing highlights. PlaybookUX is positioned as the accessible entry point for product and design teams that want to run research independently without a dedicated researcher or a large research operations budget.',
